Reference-contexts: Zenith's task is to generate features to direct the problem solver in placing controls on the network, in order ultimately to improve network performance. Several learning systems exist for TNM <ref> (Silver, et al. 1990) </ref>, one of which creates decision trees from instances using the primitive (observable) features, but feature generation for this domain has not yet been explored. In contrast to othello, there is no body of features, either human or machine generated, against which Zenith's features can be compared.
